            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EYou%20are%20promised%20victory!%20God%20is%20the%20God%20of%20peace%2C%20and%20it%20is%20His%20desire%20for%20you%20to%20have%20peace%20like%20a%20river%20in%20all%20areas%20of%20your%20life.%20Satan%20comes%20in%20to%20interrupt%20that%20peace%20and%20tranquility%2C%20but%20God%20is%20with%20you%20to%20help%20you%20crush%20Satan.%20Not%20only%20will%20you%20bruise%20him%2C%20but%20you%20will%20actually%20crush%20him!%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EBesides%20being%20promised%20that%20you%20will%20ultimately%20crush%20Satan%2C%20you%20are%20promised%20it%20will%20happen%20soon.%20This%20word%20means%20%22quickly%2C%22%20%22in%20haste%2C%22%20%22speedily%2C%22%20or%20%22shortly.%22%20God%20will%20not%20leave%20believers%20fighting%20Satan%20forever%2C%20but%20%22will%20grant%20justice%20to%20them%20quickly!%22%20(Luke%2018%3A8).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EFinally%2C%20the%20Holy%20Spirit%20describes%20the%20position%20in%20which%20Satan%20belongs%3A%20under%20your%20feet!%20Jesus%20told%20His%20disciples%2C%20%22I%20have%20given%20you%20authority%20over%20all%20the%20power%20of%20the%20enemy%2C%20and%20you%20can%20walk%20among%20snakes%20and%20scorpions%20and%20crush%20them.%20Nothing%20will%20injure%20you%22%20(Luke%2010%3A19).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EPursue%20the%20devil%20until%20he%20falls%2C%20and%20then%20crush%20him%20under%20your%20feet!%20Then%20you%20can%20boldly%20proclaim%20with%20the%20psalmist%2C%20%22I%20have%20taken%20a%20stand%2C%20and%20I%20will%20publicly%20praise%20the%20Lord%22%20(Psalm%2026%3A12).%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
