            "id": "ot-passage",
            "type": "passage",
            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "2Chr.33:14-34:33",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E2%20Chronicles%2033%3A14-34%3A33%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_33_14%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2233%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EAfter%20this%20Manasseh%20rebuilt%20the%20outer%20wall%20of%20the%20City%20of%20David%2C%20from%20west%20of%20the%20Gihon%20Spring%20in%20the%20Kidron%20Valley%20to%20the%20Fish%20Gate%2C%20and%20continuing%20around%20the%20hill%20of%20Ophel.%20He%20built%20the%20wall%20very%20high.%20And%20he%20stationed%20his%20military%20officers%20in%20all%20of%20the%20fortified%20towns%20of%20Judah.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_33_15%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2233%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EManasseh%20also%20removed%20the%20foreign%20gods%20and%20the%20idol%20from%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Temple.%20He%20tore%20down%20all%20the%20altars%20he%20had%20built%20on%20the%20hill%20where%20the%20Temple%20stood%20and%20all%20the%20altars%20that%20were%20in%20Jerusalem%2C%20and%20he%20dumped%20them%20outside%20the%20city.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_33_16%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2233%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20he%20restored%20the%20altar%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20sacrificed%20peace%20offerings%20and%20thanksgiving%20offerings%20on%20it.%20He%20also%20encouraged%20the%20people%20of%20Judah%20to%20worship%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20God%20of%20Israel.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_33_17%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2233%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EHowever%2C%20the%20people%20still%20sacrificed%20at%20the%20pagan%20shrines%2C%20though%20only%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20their%20God.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_33_18%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2233%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20rest%20of%20the%20events%20of%20Manasseh%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%2C%20his%20prayer%20to%20God%2C%20and%20the%20words%20the%20seers%20spoke%20to%20him%20in%20the%20name%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20God%20of%20Israel%2C%20are%20recorded%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Book%20of%20the%20Kings%20of%20Israel.%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_33_19%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2233%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EManasseh%26%23x2019%3Bs%20prayer%2C%20the%20account%20of%20the%20way%20God%20answered%20him%2C%20and%20an%20account%20of%20all%20his%20sins%20and%20unfaithfulness%20are%20recorded%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Record%20of%20the%20Seers.%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E33%3A19%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Record%20of%20Hozai.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20It%20includes%20a%20list%20of%20the%20locations%20where%20he%20built%20pagan%20shrines%20and%20set%20up%20Asherah%20poles%20and%20idols%20before%20he%20humbled%20himself%20and%20repented.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_33_20%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2233%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Manasseh%20died%2C%20he%20was%20buried%20in%20his%20palace.%20Then%20his%20son%20Amon%20became%20the%20next%20king.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_33_21%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2233%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EAmon%20Rules%20in%20Judah%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3EAmon%20was%20twenty-two%20years%20old%20when%20he%20became%20king%2C%20and%20he%20reigned%20in%20Jerusalem%20two%20years.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_33_22%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2233%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20did%20what%20was%20evil%20in%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sight%2C%20just%20as%20his%20father%2C%20Manasseh%2C%20had%20done.%20He%20worshiped%20and%20sacrificed%20to%20all%20the%20idols%20his%20father%20had%20made.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_33_23%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2233%22%20vn%3D%2223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E23%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20unlike%20his%20father%2C%20he%20did%20not%20humble%20himself%20before%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20Instead%2C%20Amon%20sinned%20even%20more.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_33_24%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2233%22%20vn%3D%2224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E24%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Amon%26%23x2019%3Bs%20own%20officials%20conspired%20against%20him%20and%20assassinated%20him%20in%20his%20palace.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_33_25%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2233%22%20vn%3D%2225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E25%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20the%20people%20of%20the%20land%20killed%20all%20those%20who%20had%20conspired%20against%20King%20Amon%2C%20and%20they%20made%20his%20son%20Josiah%20the%20next%20king.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_34_1%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2234%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E2%20Chronicles%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E34%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EJosiah%20Rules%20in%20Judah%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EJosiah%20was%20eight%20years%20old%20when%20he%20became%20king%2C%20and%20he%20reigned%20in%20Jerusalem%20thirty-one%20years.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_34_2%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2234%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20did%20what%20was%20pleasing%20in%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sight%20and%20followed%20the%20example%20of%20his%20ancestor%20David.%20He%20did%20not%20turn%20away%20from%20doing%20what%20was%20right.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_34_3%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2234%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EDuring%20the%20eighth%20year%20of%20his%20reign%2C%20while%20he%20was%20still%20young%2C%20Josiah%20began%20to%20seek%20the%20God%20of%20his%20ancestor%20David.%20Then%20in%20the%20twelfth%20year%20he%20began%20to%20purify%20Judah%20and%20Jerusalem%2C%20destroying%20all%20the%20pagan%20shrines%2C%20the%20Asherah%20poles%2C%20and%20the%20carved%20idols%20and%20cast%20images.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_34_4%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2234%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20ordered%20that%20the%20altars%20of%20Baal%20be%20demolished%20and%20that%20the%20incense%20altars%20which%20stood%20above%20them%20be%20broken%20down.%20He%20also%20made%20sure%20that%20the%20Asherah%20poles%2C%20the%20carved%20idols%2C%20and%20the%20cast%20images%20were%20smashed%20and%20scattered%20over%20the%20graves%20of%20those%20who%20had%20sacrificed%20to%20them.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_34_5%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2234%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20burned%20the%20bones%20of%20the%20pagan%20priests%20on%20their%20own%20altars%2C%20and%20so%20he%20purified%20Judah%20and%20Jerusalem.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_34_6%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2234%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20did%20the%20same%20thing%20in%20the%20towns%20of%20Manasseh%2C%20Ephraim%2C%20and%20Simeon%2C%20even%20as%20far%20as%20Naphtali%2C%20and%20in%20the%20regions%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E34%3A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20Syriac%20version%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3Ein%20their%20temples%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20%3Cem%3Ein%20their%20ruins.%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20meaning%20of%20the%20Hebrew%20is%20uncertain.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20all%20around%20them.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_34_7%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2234%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20destroyed%20the%20pagan%20altars%20and%20the%20Asherah%20poles%2C%20and%20he%20crushed%20the%20idols%20into%20dust.%20He%20cut%20down%20all%20the%20incense%20altars%20throughout%20the%20land%20of%20Israel.%20Finally%2C%20he%20returned%20to%20Jerusalem.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_34_8%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2234%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EIn%20the%20eighteenth%20year%20of%20his%20reign%2C%20after%20he%20had%20purified%20the%20land%20and%20the%20Temple%2C%20Josiah%20appointed%20Shaphan%20son%20of%20Azaliah%2C%20Maaseiah%20the%20governor%20of%20Jerusalem%2C%20and%20Joah%20son%20of%20Joahaz%2C%20the%20royal%20historian%2C%20to%20repair%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20his%20God.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_34_9%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2234%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20gave%20Hilkiah%20the%20high%20priest%20the%20money%20that%20had%20been%20collected%20by%20the%20Levites%20who%20served%20as%20gatekeepers%20at%20the%20Temple%20of%20God.%20The%20gifts%20were%20brought%20by%20people%20from%20Manasseh%2C%20Ephraim%2C%20and%20from%20all%20the%20remnant%20of%20Israel%2C%20as%20well%20as%20from%20all%20Judah%2C%20Benjamin%2C%20and%20the%20people%20of%20Jerusalem.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_34_10%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2234%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20entrusted%20the%20money%20to%20the%20men%20assigned%20to%20supervise%20the%20restoration%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Temple.%20Then%20they%20paid%20the%20workers%20who%20did%20the%20repairs%20and%20renovation%20of%20the%20Temple.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_34_11%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2234%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20hired%20carpenters%20and%20builders%2C%20who%20purchased%20finished%20stone%20for%20the%20walls%20and%20timber%20for%20the%20rafters%20and%20beams.%20They%20restored%20what%20earlier%20kings%20of%20Judah%20had%20allowed%20to%20fall%20into%20ruin.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_34_12%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2234%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20workers%20served%20faithfully%20under%20the%20leadership%20of%20Jahath%20and%20Obadiah%2C%20Levites%20of%20the%20Merarite%20clan%2C%20and%20Zechariah%20and%20Meshullam%2C%20Levites%20of%20the%20Kohathite%20clan.%20Other%20Levites%2C%20all%20of%20whom%20were%20skilled%20musicians%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_34_13%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2234%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3Ewere%20put%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20laborers%20of%20the%20various%20trades.%20Still%20others%20assisted%20as%20secretaries%2C%20officials%2C%20and%20gatekeepers.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_34_14%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2234%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EHilkiah%20Discovers%20God%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Law%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EWhile%20they%20were%20bringing%20out%20the%20money%20collected%20at%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Temple%2C%20Hilkiah%20the%20priest%20found%20the%20Book%20of%20the%20Law%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20that%20was%20written%20by%20Moses.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_34_15%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2234%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EHilkiah%20said%20to%20Shaphan%20the%20court%20secretary%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BI%20have%20found%20the%20Book%20of%20the%20Law%20in%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Temple!%26%23x201D%3B%20Then%20Hilkiah%20gave%20the%20scroll%20to%20Shaphan.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_34_16%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2234%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EShaphan%20took%20the%20scroll%20to%20the%20king%20and%20reported%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BYour%20officials%20are%20doing%20everything%20they%20were%20assigned%20to%20do.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_34_17%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2234%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20money%20that%20was%20collected%20at%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20has%20been%20turned%20over%20to%20the%20supervisors%20and%20workmen.%26%23x201D%3B%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_34_18%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2234%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C